-- German Minister Wants Tax Cuts Before 2013 Election, Rheinische Post Says
-- Holger Elfes
-- 2010-07-20T22:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/german-minister-wants-tax-cuts-before-2013-election-rheinische-post-says.html

          
          
             German Development Minister Dirk
Niebel said his Free Democratic Party wants tax cuts before the
next federal elections in 2013,  Rheinische Post  reported, citing
an interview with the minister.  
 The government may cancel some tax privileges in exchange,
the newspaper said in an e-mailed preview of an article to be
published today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Holger Elfes  in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net .  
          
          


  


        